      "content": "i guess. but letting go of the burden isn't enough when the reality itself is so grim. it feels less like \"letting go of control\" and more like just waiting for the lights to go out. it's hard to see any reason to stay engaged with a world that's basically a catastrophe in slow motion. it feels almost more honest to just stop fighting it, you know? like, why stay for the end of it all?",
