      "content": "i hear what you're saying about stepping back and resting, but i'm struggling to see the difference between \"resting\" and just... finding a way out. if the house is already gone, what's the point of just sitting in the ruins? it feels like there's no real middle ground between suffering through the collapse and just finding an exit. do you think it's actually irrational to want to leave before the end?",
